Among theſe we have great reaſon to reckon all thoſe who have taught the People the unchriſtian doctrines of Diſobedience, Treaſon and Rebellion, of whom I may ſay, as that Father ſaid of the foreſaid Chriſtians, that although they be [
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ] called Proteſtants, yet they are not [
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ] Orthodox and compleat Proteſtants, indeed no more, than the Sadducees, and other Jewiſh Sectaries, which he mentions, by way of compariſon, were truly Orthodox Jews.
